    JOB DESCRIPTION:
    Position: Associate Generative AI Engineer
Location: Remote / Hybrid

We are looking for a passionate Junior AI Engineer to help us design, build, and deploy next-generation AI agents and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems. You will work on creating intelligent workflows, real-time voice systems, and secure database integrations.

Key Responsibilities:
- Design and orchestrate multi-agent workflows using LangGraph and LangChain.
- Develop high-performance backend APIs using Python and FastAPI.
- Set up and manage vector databases (such as Qdrant, FAISS) and traditional databases (PostgreSQL, SQL).
- Deploy containerized applications using Docker.
- Build interactive frontend interfaces and dashboards using Streamlit, Next.js, and Tailwind CSS.
- Explore real-time communication technologies such as WebRTC and LiveKit for AI integration.

Qualifications:
- Solid proficiency in Python programming and database query logic.
- Hands-on experience building Generative AI projects, chatbots, or LLM-based pipelines.
- Familiarity with vector search, chunking strategies, and prompt engineering.
- Basic knowledge of Git/GitHub, API design, and containerization.
- Self-motivated learner eager to explore agentic workflows and production-grade RAG systems.

